The article is a transcript of a press briefing from October 19, 2017. The briefing began with Sarah Sanders sharing a letter from a seven-year-old girl named Mackenzie who expressed her admiration for President Trump. Sanders announced that the President had invited Mackenzie to visit the White House during her spring break. The briefing then shifted to a more serious topic, with General Kelly addressing questions about outreach to Gold Star families. He explained the process that takes place when a service member is killed in combat and how the President typically reaches out to the families. Kelly also criticized a member of Congress for listening in on a phone call between the President and a Gold Star widow and for using the moment for political gain. He emphasized the importance of keeping the sacrifices made by service members sacred. Kelly also answered questions about the incident in Niger and the ongoing investigation. The briefing concluded with Kelly expressing his appreciation for the men and women serving in the military.